RISC-V RVV fractional LMUL check is wrong

At commit 7aa4d519, HELPER(vsetvl)'s check for fractional LMUL was changed incorrectly, and can end up shifting by a negative value for element, in practice resulting in vsetvli setting vill when it shouldn't.
For example, the instruction vsetvli s2, x0, e8, mf2, ta, ma on a latest master build ends up at target/riscv/vector_helper.c doing:

cpu->cfg.vlenb >> (8 - 3 - vlmul) < sew // the check in HELPER(vsetvl)
cpu->cfg.vlenb >> (8 - 3 - 7) < sew
cpu->cfg.vlenb >> (-2) < sew


A fix can be to replace that expression with (cpu->cfg.vlenb << 3) >> (8 - vlmul) < sew, as listed within a comment in the code before the incorrect simplification.
